ï»¿# SupertropicalPy

[![Python Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.8+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green.svg)](LICENSE)
[![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/TetewHeroez/supertropicalpy/blob/main/docs/source/examples/tutorial.ipynb)

A comprehensive Python package for **supertropical algebra**, featuring tangible and ghost elements, matrix operations, and linear system solving using Cramer's rule.

> **ğŸš€ Try it now!** Click the "Open in Colab" badge above to run the interactive tutorial instantly in your browser - fast and free! No installation needed.

## âœ¨ Features

- **ğŸ¯ Tangible & Ghost Elements**: Full support for both element types with automatic conversion

- **ğŸ§® Supertropical Operations**: Addition $\oplus$ defined by $a\oplus b=\max\{a,b\}$ (with ghost rules), and multiplication $\odot$ defined by $a\odot b=a+b$.

- **ğŸ“ Matrix Operations**: Matrix multiplication, permanent (supertropical determinant), adjoint.

- **ğŸ”§ Linear System Solver**: Cramer's rule implementation for solving $Ax = b$

- **ğŸš€ NumPy Integration**: Efficient computations using NumPy arrays

- **ğŸ“š Comprehensive Documentation**: Full API reference, theory guide, and interactive tutorials

- **âœ… Type Safety**: Automatic type coercion and validation

